Does high satisfaction lead to higher prices?

Determinants of Airbnb Prices in Istanbul and Barcelona

Sla Erikci

METU Department of Economics

June 2019

About

In recent years, a new business model known as the sharing economy has become a major phenomenon. This concept has emerged in the accommodation sector of the tourism and hospitality. Airbnb, like many other platforms (Uber, Spotify, Lyft), has pioneered the use of this business model to connect people who own idle accommodation assets such as empty rooms or apartments with those who need temporary accommodation like tourists via digital platforms. Thus, many people have started to participate in sharing economy platforms because of the economic and financial benefits it provides both for suppliers and consumers. In particular, these platforms provide cost-saving benefits and convenience to the consumers, while allowing suppliers to generate extra income. Therefore, one of the reason for the rapid growth of sharing economy based accommodation rental has been attributed to the provision of a wide range of prices and property features, as well as a more diversified experience than that of conventional hotel accommodation (Guttentag, 2015; Tussyadiah and Pesonen, 2015; Wang et al., 2016). Since the market share of this multi-sided platform in accomodation sector is rapidly increasing, discussing what customers value most in Airbnb accommodations and what price determinants are in this marketplace would be highly reasonable.

In the conventional hotel industry, most of the factors determining the price of hotel accomodation are known by both guests and hotel owners. Location, number of stars, amenities such as mini bar, TV, hair dryer and laundry services such as breakfast services are some of the most common ones. However, factors determining prices in Airbnb are much more complex. As consumers care social benefits as much as economic benefits, they may perceive differently the value of services offered through sharing economy platforms than they do the value of traditional businesses. For example, consumers may value the communication, trustworthiness, and friendliness of their Airbnb hosts and the experience they enjoy during their stay (Mody, Suess, & Lehto, in press). In addition, as a feedback and self-selection mechanism of Airbnb, when customers leave the house, they can write review and rate their experience on the website of the house by evaluating cleanliness of room, location, communication of host, accuracy of information before reservation, value of the room and check-in experience. All these ratings can give information about consumers overall satisfaction. This study investigates effects of overall satisfaction on prices and shows that its effect is not always positively related with price of the rooms per night by comparing two important tourism center, stanbul and Barcelona.

Data

Data Source

  • insideairbnb.com
  • Downloaded on 5 April 2019
  • Listings date compiled is March 2019

Variables

  • Price (turkish lira for Istanbul, euro for Barcelona)
  • Room type (Entire home/apartment & Private)
  • Number of bedrooms
  • Host name
  • Host gender (by gender(host_name) function)
  • Superhost status (true/false)
  • Host identity verified (true/false)
  • Host has profile picture (true/false)
  • Review scores for
    • cleanliness
    • location
    • communication
    • accuracy
    • value
    • check-in
  • Overall satisfaction (average of review scores rating)
  • Cancellation policy (flexible/non-flexible)
  • Instant bookable (true/false)
  • Longitude
  • Latitude

Descriptives

Property Attributes

Since Istanbul and Barcelona are among the most touristy cities in the world, there are many rental houses all over the city, especially in central locations. The locations in the graph are drawn according to the latitude and longitude values of the houses and approximately 7 thousand houses were used for Istanbul and 10 thousand houses for Barcelona.

In Airbnb listings, houses are defined in three types: entire home/apartment, private room and shared room. However, since the share of shared room is very low compared to the others, it was not included in the study. The distribution of house types is as follows for both cities:

As can be seen from the graphs, the share of entire home is higher in Istanbul, while the share of private room is higher in both cities, but in both cities the average price is higher for entire home type.

Model

  • Model:

log(price) ~ bedrooms + gender + profile.pic + superhost + identity.verif + satisfaction + cancellation.policy + instant.bookable

Coefficient of independent variables times 100 shows percentage change in per night prices. Based on the previous literature on sharing economy based accommodation rentals and hotel price determinants, the effects of 8 variables in the following 4 categories are examined:property attributes, host attributes, rental rules and online review ratings.

Diagnostics

The residual diagnostics are used for testing and detecting of standard regression assumptions.

The following plots indicate that there is no serious violation of regression assumption and model is good for estimation:

  • Residuals vs Fitted plot shows the residuals spread randomly around the 0 line indicating that the relationship is fairly linear and no residual is visibly away from the random pattern indicating that there are no outliers.

  • Normal Q-Q plot shows that residuals are distributed as random enough.

  • Scale-Location plot shows that residuals are spread equally enough along the ranges of predictors.

  • Residuals vs Leverage plot shows there is no influential cases.

Results

Results and key findings of the 4 regressions can be summarized as follows:

  • Number of bedrooms in entire home/apartment has significantly large effect on prices, 15.1% and 13.6% in Istanbul and Barcelona respectively.

  • Male hosts have positive effect on prices by 6.7% only in private rooms in Barcelona. Although both number of private rooms and female hosts are greater than number of entire home and male hosts in Barcelona, reason might be that supply of private rooms provided by male host is less than 23% share.

  • There is no significant gender difference in Istanbul.

  • Hosts having profile pictures are decreasing prices by 85%. This result is not reliable since there is only 5 host whose profile picture does not exist.

  • Superhost increases prices by 7% in Barcelona for each room type and by 10.1% in Istanbul for only entire home.

  • Hosts whose identity is verified increase prices about 11.3% for private rooms and 5.2% for entire home in Istanbul. This is highly important factor on prices due to trustworthiness of host.

  • Non-flexible cancellation policy lead to higher prices for each room type in each city (13.7% for private rooms in stanbul. As flexible cancellation policies and low prices are related, it seems that for those hosts who set flexibility in cancellation are driven by emotional factors rather that rational element: they do not care much about securing income,they just wantto obtain a fair price and from those guests who really want to come (and if they decide not to come at the last minute this is not an issue)

  • Instant bookable feature has more positive effects on prices in Istanbul than Barcelona. It is a positive amenity that helps the guests plan their trip in an easier way and increases prices by 13.6% for private room in Istanbul, by 4% for entire home in Barcelona.

  • Interesting point is about effect of overall satisfaction for private rooms in Istanbul. According to straightforward economics theory, if expected utility of consumers is higher, then they demand more and priceses become higher eventually. However, this is not the case in Istanbul.(Increase in satisfaction leads to lower price by 2.6%) Unlike positive impact of overall satisfaction on prices in Barcelona, this variable has declining effect in Istanbul. For private rooms there, it is obvious that number of bedrooms, verified host identity, non-flexible cancellation policy and feature of instant bookable have positively significant effect on prices. When we think incidence of these factors on consumers satisfaction, it can be said strict effects of cancellation policy and instant bookable features can compansate each other because both have approximately. In terms of trustworthiness of host, higher the number of verified hosts higher satisfaction consumers get. Even though verification of identit of host has substantially high importance on prices of private rooms, less than 10% of hosts identity is verified. Therefore, hosts having non-verified identity may tend to improve other features, so prices, of home to compansate lower satisfaction level. Another reason might be like following: since Airbnb is relatively new platform in Turkey compared to Europe, review scores, may not be effective feedback mechanism for hosts yet and may be poor indicator for consumers.Indeed, for the entire home/apartments in Istanbul, no significant effect of satisfaction is observed. The effect of review scores is positively related with price as expected. Priced are increased by 2% for private room and 7% for entire home/apartment.
